Head coach <Tyronn Lue/> will be on the sideline Wednesday night when his Cleveland Cavaliers face the Minnesota Timberwolves, a source tells ESPN's <Dave McMenamin/>.

<Lue/> left Tuesday night's 116-98 loss to the Orlando Magic because of an illness and did not return.

<Lue/> also missed a game Dec. 21 against the Chicago Bulls with an undisclosed illness, needing to stay in the locker room after already arriving to the arena and going through his pregame media duties.

The Cavaliers (30-22) have lost three of their past four games and enter Wednesday in third place in the Eastern Conference.